{"title_page": "Borot\u00edn (Blansko District)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Borot\u00edn\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=Borotin (zamek).JPG\n|image_shield=Borotin BK CZ CoA.svg\n|image_flag=Borotin BK CZ flag.svg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[South Moravian Region|South Moravian]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Blansko District|Blansko]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|49|34|55|N|16|40|32|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=7.62\n|population_total=424\n|population_as_of=2012\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=420\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=679&nbsp;37\n|website=http://www.obecborotin.cz\n}}\n\n'''Borot\u00edn''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Blansko District]] in the [[South Moravian Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|7.62|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 431 (as at 28&nbsp;August 2006).\n\nBorot\u00edn lies approximately {{convert|24|km|mi|0}} north of [[Blansko]], {{convert|43|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north of [[Brno]], and {{convert|172|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} east of [[Prague]].\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Borot\u00edn (Blansko District)}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071011015850/http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0621 Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Blansko District]\n\n{{Blansko District}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Borotin}}\n[[Category:Villages in Blansko District]]\n\n\n{{SouthMoravia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Borot\u00edn\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=Borotin (zamek).JPG\n|image_shield=Borotin BK CZ CoA.svg\n|image_flag=Borotin BK CZ flag.svg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic