{"title_page": "Borotice (Znojmo District)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Borotice\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=\n|image_shield=Borotice_ZN_CZ_CoA.jpg\n|image_flag=Borotice_ZN_CZ_flag.png\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[South Moravian Region|South Moravian]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Znojmo District|Znojmo]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|48|51|26|N|16|14|33|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=12.06\n|population_total=428\n|population_as_of=1.1.2012\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=197\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=671&nbsp;65\n|website=http://www.borotice.cz\n}}\n\n'''Borotice''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Znojmo District]] in the [[South Moravian Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|12.06|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 386 (as at 3&nbsp;July 2006).\n\nBorotice lies on the [[Jevi\u0161ovka River]], approximately {{convert|16|km|mi|0}} east of [[Znojmo]], {{convert|47|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-west of [[Brno]], and {{convert|190|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081211035327/http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0627/ Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Znojmo District]\n\n{{commons category|Borotice (Znojmo District)}}\n{{Znojmo District}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Borotice}}\n[[Category:Villages in Znojmo District]]\n\n\n{{SouthMoravia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Borotice\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=\n|image_shield=Borotice_ZN_CZ_CoA.jpg\n|image_flag=Borotice_ZN_CZ_flag.png\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivisi